  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and execute marine engineering projects such as ship repair, shipbuilding, offshore structures, and marine equipment installation.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with ship owners, clients, classification societies, and port authorities to ensure project requirements are met.</p></li><li><p>Prepare project schedules, work plans, method statements, and technical documentation.</p></li><li><p>Supervise onboard and yard activities including fabrication, installation, commissioning, and testing of marine systems.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with marine safety regulations, class rules (ABS, DNV, LR, BV), and international standards.</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, quality, cost control, and timelines; report any deviations to management.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with subcontractors, vendors, and suppliers for materials, manpower, and equipment.</p></li><li><p>Conduct inspections, attend surveys, and support class/flag state approvals.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper implementation of HSE (Health, Safety & Environment) procedures at work sites.</p></li><li><p>Prepare progress reports, technical reports, and project handover documentation.</p></li><li><p>Support troubleshooting and rectification of technical issues during project execution.</p></li><li><p>Assist in project budgeting, cost estimation, and variation order management.</p></li></ul>",
